<section><title>Practice: troubleshooting tools</title>
	<para>0. It is imperative that you practice these tools <command>before</command> trouble arises. It will help you get familiar with the tools and allow you to create a base line of normal behaviour for your systems.</para>
	<para>1. Read the theory on <command>fuser</command> and explore its man page. Use this command to find files that you open yourself.</para>
	<para>2. Read the theory on <command>lsof</command> and explore its man page. Use this command to find files that you open yourself.</para>
	<para>3. Boot a live image on an existing computer (virtual or real) and <command>chroot</command> into to it.</para>
	<para>4. Start one or more disk intensive jobs and monitor them with <command>iostat</command> and <command>iotop</command> (compare to <command>vmstat</command>).</para>
</section>

